data.title: CityTrip
data.text:
Prescott - Territorial Arizona's Capital City - From Phoenix - Private Tour

Itinerary

This is a typical itinerary for this productShow More

Stop At: Sharlot Hall Museum, 415 W. Gurley St. Two blocks west from Courthouse Plaza and Whiskey Row, Prescott, AZ 86301-3691

Explore the grounds and buildings of this beautiful museum. Your entrance fee is covered in this tour. There is a large amount of information on not only Prescott, Arizona's first capital, but also surrounding Yavapai County and the state of Arizona.

Duration: 1 hour

Stop At: The Palace Restaurant and Saloon, 120 S Montezuma St, Prescott, AZ 86303-4718

For lunch you will be experiencing this historic location. Located in the heart of "Whiskey Row" - According to USA today, "One of the Top 10 Historic Bars in America" This is truly a destinations meal! (Cost of lunch is included up to $20 per person). You might want to watch the movie "Junior Bonner" with Steve McQueen as it was filmed here.

Duration: 1 hour 30 minutes

Stop At: Whiskey Row, N Montezuma St, Prescott, AZ 86301

You will have a chance to spend a bit of time roaming this historic town square.

Duration: 30 minutes

Stop At: Phippen Museum, 4701 Highway 89 North, Prescott, AZ 86301

This wonderful western art museum is located on the outskirts of Prescott, very near where many westerns were filmed during the 1920's. The exhibits change each season, so you get a variety of types a artwork in this beautiful location.

Duration: 1 hour

Stop At: Museum of Indigenous People, 147 N Arizona Ave, Prescott, AZ 86301-3184

This can be an option stop instead of going to the art museum if you like. Now called The Museum of the Indigenous People, is the only museum in the greater Prescott area devoted to the culture and art of Native people. This very historic little museum houses many interesting cultural items from the early residents of Arizona. The museum building was completed in 1935.

Duration: 30 minutes
